                <note rend="inline" type="source">763.72119P43/536: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Commission to Negotiate Peace</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-07-25T17:00:00-04:00"
                            >July 25, 1919—5 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2634. Your 3227, July 19th, 7 p.m. Mr. Polk has with him individual document of
                    appointment and full power conferring same powers as given commissioners in
                    joint document of November 30th<note n="72" xml:id="d298fn72">
                        <ref target="frus1919Parisv01#pg_175">Vol. <hi rend="smallcaps">i</hi>, p.
                            175</ref>.</note> which Department understands still in effect as
                    regards commissioners remaining in Paris.</p>
                <p>Department concurs in your views as to powers Commissioners to sign treaties with
                    Bulgaria and Turkey and regards present powers as sufficient.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
